definition.value: A member of the class of acetamides that is acetamide in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen has been replaced by an aryl-substituted alkyl group.
A CMP-N-acyl-beta-neuraminic acid in which the N-acyl group is glycoloyl.
An alcohol that consists of cyclohexane bearing a single hydroxy substituent. The parent of the class of cyclohexanols.
